NOTES

HTML TERMS
ELEMENTS
TAGS (OPENING / CLOSING)
ATTRIBUTES (NAME VALUE)
VALUES

HTML:
-> ELEMENT:
h1
a

-> TAG:
<a> </a>

a = element
<a> = opening tag
</a> = closing tag
<a href="bafsf"> </a>
href = attribute
"bafsf" = value



CSS:
TERMS
SELECTOR
PROPERTY
VALUE

Selector: selects which elements to target
followed by brackets which define the properties;

p = { }

PROPERTY SAMPLE:
color: value;
background: something;

value and something are "values"


SELECTORS:
TYPE SELECTOR: ALL ELEMENTS OF THAT TYPE
div = { }
a = {}

CLASS SELECTOR:
.classname = { }

classname = find all html elements who have the class attribute set to classname and then apply the properties

ID SELECTOR:
#idname = { }
FIND THE HTML ELEMENT WHICH HAS THE ID ELEMENT SET TO idname and then apply properties


LINKING HTML AND CSS:
IN HTML -> LINK STYLESHEET
in head: 
<link rel="stylesheet" href="main.css">
SO:
ELEMENT: LINK
ATTRIBUTE: REL (RELATIONSHIP) VALUE stylesheet
ATTRIBUTE href VALUE main.css
NOTE: /main.css = site.com/main.css

CLASS SELECTION: ADVANCED
ID > CLASS > TYPE (prio)

.class .otherclass 
-> select all elements classname class
--> then select from all remaining classname otherclass

COLORS:
-> keyword
-> hex
-> rgb / hsl / rgba (alpha / transp.)

Length;
pixels (offset)
relative::
%
em = element font size


BOX:
margin - border - padding - content
set size:
1 value : all 4 sides
2 values: top/bottom, left/right
4 values: top right bottom left


BORDERS:
color, style, width ARE NECESSRARY
border: <widht> <style> <color>
STYLE: a lot, solid, dashed, dotted.. etc
p {
	border: 6px solid rgb(0,0,0);
}

Certain ways of box sizign;
content-box:
normal sizing
padding-box;
now padding is in the size;
increasing padding shrinks content
increasing border only increases border and thus size of element
border-box;
border also in size. k.
